CSS
Cascading Style Sheet

.Syntax
--------
p{color:blue;}

p = selector
{color:blue;} = declaration
 color = property
 blue  = value

 Connection
 Inline Css (Tag အတွင်း ချိတ်)
 <h1 style="color:green;>Heading one</h1>

 Internal Css (head tag တွင် style နဲ့ ချိတ်)
 <style>
 p{
    color: red;
    font-size: 20px;
 }
 </style>
 
 External Css (Link နဲ့ ချိတ်)
 .To do file create(style.css)
 .to use link tag file နဲ့ ချိတ်ရန် <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">

 Css selector
 -------------
 .By html tag name
 .Class(class name cann't start with a number)
 .Id(Unique Value) Note: Id name cann't start with a number.

 <div> tag => အုပ်စုဖွဲ့လိုတဲ့ခါ သုံး
 Display Property
 Block Element  =>  1 line မှာ တစ်ခုပဲ ရေးလို့ရ၊width/height မသတ်မှတ်ထားရင် အပြည့်ယူ၊သူ့နောက်မှာ ကပ်ပြီးလိုက်တာမရှိ(html/css) တစ်ကြောင်းစီဖြစ်သွားမယ်။
 Inline Element =>  တစ်ခုပြီးတစ်ခု 1 line ထဲမှာ ရေးလို့ရ။
 
 Block Element 
 -----------------
<div>,<h1> - <h6>,<p>,<form>,<header>,<footer><section>,ul,ol,li,table,fieldset,figure,figcaption
Inline Element
--------------
span,a,button,input,label,select,teextarea,b,i,img,br,small,em...

Content - The content of the box, where text and images appear
Padding - Clears an area around the content. The padding is transparent
Border  - A border that goes around the padding and content
Margin  - Clears an area outside the border. The margin is transparent

underline ဖျောက်ချင်=> text-decoration: none;
Browser မှ သတ်မှတ်သော color ကို မလိုလျှင်=> color:inherit;
Margin/Padding
---------------------
the margin shorthand property with four values:

margin: 25px 50px 75px 100px;

.top margin is 25px
.right margin is 50px
.bottom margin is 75px
.left margin is 100px

margin: 25px 50px 75px;
.top margin is 25px
.right and left margins are 50px
.bottom margin is 75px

margin: 25px 50px;
.top and bottom margins are 25px
.right and left margins are 50px

margin: 25px;
.all four margins are 25px

height and width Values
--------------------------
The height and width properties may have the following values:
auto     -> This is default. The browser calculates the height and width
length   ->Defines the height/width in px, cm, etc.
%        -> Defines the height/width in percent of the containing block
initial  -> Sets the height/width to its default value
inherit  -> The height/width will be inherited from its parent value

All CSS Dimension Properties
----------------------------
Property	Description
height	   -> Sets the height of an element
max-height  ->	Sets the maximum height of an element
max-width   ->	Sets the maximum width of an element
min-height  ->	Sets the minimum height of an element
min-width   ->	Sets the minimum width of an element
width	      -> Sets the width of an element

Text Color
------------
The color property is used to set the color of the text.

Text Decoration Properties
---------------------------------
text-decoration-line       = >add a decoration line to text.
text-decoration-color      = >the color of the decoration line.
text-decoration-style      = >the style of the decoration line.
text-decoration-thickness  = >the thickness of the decoration line.
text-decoration            = >is a shorthand property for:

Text Transformation
------------------------
text-transform property = >uppercase and lowercase letters in a text.
text-transform:uppercase; = > THIS IS TRANSFORM TO uppercase
text-transform:lowercase; = > this is transform to lowercase
text-transform:capitalize; = > This Is Transform To Capitalize

Text Spacing properties
-------------
text-indent       = >the indentation of the first line of a text:
letter-spacing    = >the space between the characters in a text.
line-height       = >the space between lines:
word-spacing      = >the space between the words in a text.
white-space       = >specifies how white-space inside an element is handled.

Text Shadow
-----------
text-shadow: 2px 2px;
text-shadow property adds shadow to text.

Styling Links
--------------------
a:link - a normal, unvisited link
a:visited - a link the user has visited
a:hover - a link when the user mouses over it
a:active - a link the moment it is clicked

Lists
-------------------
Unordered Lists: Ordered Lists:
list-style-type property  = >specifies the type of list item marker.
ul.a {
  list-style-type: circle;
}
list-style-image property = >specifies an image as the list item marker:
ul {
  list-style-image: url('sqpurple.gif');
}
list-style-position property specifies the position of the list-item markers (bullet points).
ul.a {
  list-style-position: outside;inside;
}

The display Property
----------------------
display property = > specify how an element is shown on a web page.

The z-index Property
--------------------
z-index:-1; //behind th text

The float Property
------------------
The float property is used for positioning and formatting content e.g. let an image float left to the text in a container.
Float propertie's value
float:left; //The element floats to the left of its container
float:right; //The element floats to the right of its container.
float:none; //The element does not float (will be displayed just where it occurs in the text). This is default
float:inherit; //The element inherits the float value of its parent

list-style-type: none; - Removes the bullets. A navigation bar does not need list markers
Set margin: 0; and padding: 0; to remove browser default settings

